The paper discusses the use of the Arts & Humanities Citation Index (A&HCI) for journal mapping, which involves analyzing citation patterns between journals. This falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the analysis of references to journals in the Science Citation Index (cs.IR) and Social Science Citation Index (cs.SI), which are both related to information retrieval. Finally, the paper discusses the topic of "digital humanities" (cs.CL), which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on the application of computational methods to humanities research.
